      <p>Based on real Wichita market data. A fair, honest number.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-box">
      <div class="icon">🗓</div>
      <h3>Close in 7 Days</h3>
      <p>Or on your schedule. You pick the closing date.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-box">
      <div class="icon">💰</div>
      <h3>Zero Fees</h3>
      <p>No agent commissions. No closing costs. What we offer is what you get.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-box">
      <div class="icon">🔨</div>
      <h3>No Repairs</h3>
      <p>Sell as-is. Leave whatever you don't want behind.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>What We Can Do</h2>
  <p>We can work alongside the estate's attorney, accommodate court-approved timelines, and purchase the property in any condition. If the estate needs flexibility, we provide it. If speed is important, we can move quickly once probate allows.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Work alongside probate attorneys</li>
    <li>Flexible on timeline as court requires</li>
    <li>Buy property in any condition</li>
    <li>No repairs, cleaning, or staging</li>
    <li>Close through a local Wichita title company</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Honest Trade-Off</h2>
  <p>A cash offer will typically be below full retail market value — that's the trade-off for speed, certainty, and zero prep costs. But when you factor in commissions (5–6%), repair costs, carrying costs during a 60–90 day listing, and the risk of deals falling through — a fair cash offer often puts more money in your pocket than you'd expect.</p>
  <p>We'll always give you a straight answer. If the traditional route is actually better for your situation, we'll tell you that.</p>

  <h2>How It Works</h2>
  <div class="steps-list">
    <div class="step-row">
      <div class="step-circle">1</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h3>Call or Text (316) 368-3344</h3>
        <p>Tell us about your situation and your property. Takes 5 minutes, zero obligation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-row">
